---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Container from '../components/layout/Container.astro';
import Section from '../components/layout/Section.astro';
import Divider from '../components/ui/Divider.astro';
import SmartImage from '../components/media/SmartImage.astro';
import JsonLd from '../components/seo/JsonLd.astro';
import { breadcrumbLD } from '../lib/jsonld';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Samadhi Retreats has built a small collection of boutique resorts and restaurants across Malaysia since 1999."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <JsonLd data={breadcrumbLD([{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'About', href: '/about' }])} />
  </Fragment>

  <Section tone="cream">
    <Container narrow>
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-clay-600 mb-3">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-display-xl font-display">Small places, done slowly.</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-forest-700 leading-relaxed">
        We began in 1999 with a single house on Persiaran Madge in Kuala Lumpur. The idea was modest: build a place that felt like a kampung, in the middle of the city, and host guests the way our grandparents would have hosted them — quietly, carefully, without fuss.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-forest-700 leading-relaxed">
        A quarter century later, the collection is still small: two resorts, five restaurants, and no plans to grow beyond what we can oversee in person. Each property is built by local craftspeople from local materials, and each kitchen is led by chefs we have known and trained for years.
      </p>
    </Container>
  </Section>

  <Section tone="cream" class="pt-0">
    <Container>
      <div class="grid gap-3 grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4">
        <SmartImage src="about-1" source="picsum" alt="A hand-woven atap roof at close range" variant="gallery" aspect="gallery-portrait" />
        <SmartImage src="about-2" source="picsum" alt="Cooking over a charcoal fire" variant="gallery" aspect="gallery-landscape" />
        <SmartImage src="about-3" source="picsum" alt="A lantern against dusk sky" variant="gallery" aspect="gallery-square" />
        <SmartImage src="about-4" source="picsum" alt="Teak timber being planed by hand" variant="gallery" aspect="gallery-portrait" />
      </div>
    </Container>
  </Section>

  <Section tone="sand">
    <Container narrow>
      <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest-900">Built by hand</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-forest-700/90">Every property is designed and built by local architects and craftspeople. Nothing is modular. Nothing is replicated.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest-900">Cooked with the source</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-forest-700/90">Our kitchens source from Malaysian growers and fishers. Menus shift with the seasons and the weather.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-forest-900">Run quietly</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-forest-700/90">We do not run chains. Every guest is greeted by a team that knows the property and the kitchens inside out.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <Divider class="my-12" />
      <p class="text-center text-sm italic text-forest-700/70 max-w-prose mx-auto">
        Samadhi, in Sanskrit, is the state of complete attention — the moment when the mind settles fully into what is in front of it. That is the idea we are still chasing.
      </p>
    </Container>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
